## Form Elements

### Modern Input Fields
```css
.input {
  /* Clean foundation */
  background: white;
  border: 1px solid #e2e8f0;
  border-radius: 0.375rem;
  padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
  
  /* Typography */
  font-size: 1rem;
  color: #1a202c;
  
  /* Modern transitions */
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
}

.input:focus {
  outline: none;
  border-color: #3a7ca5;
  box-shadow: 0 0 0 3px rgba(58, 124, 165, 0.1);
  background: #fafafa;
}

.input::placeholder {
  color: #a0aec0;
  font-weight: 400;
}
```

### Floating Labels (Modern Pattern)
```css
.floatingLabel {
  position: relative;
}

.floatingLabel input:focus + label,
.floatingLabel input:not(:placeholder-shown) + label {
  transform: translateY(-1.5rem) scale(0.875);
  color: #3a7ca5;
}

.floatingLabel label {
  position: absolute;
  top: 0.75rem;
  left: 1rem;
  transition: all 0.2s ease;
  background: white;
  padding: 0 0.25rem;
}
```

## Navigation & Headers

### Modern Navigation
```css
.navigation {
  /* Glass effect */
  background: rgba(255, 255, 255, 0.95);
  backdrop-filter: blur(20px);
  
  /* Minimal border */
  border-bottom: 1px solid rgba(0, 0, 0, 0.05);
  
  /* Sticky behavior */
  position: sticky;
  top: 0;
  z-index: 100;
}

.navLink {
  /* Modern link styling */
  position: relative;
  color: #4a5568;
  font-weight: 500;
  padding: 0.5rem 1rem;
  transition: color 0.2s ease;
}

.navLink::after {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  bottom: 0;
  left: 0;
  width: 0;
  height: 2px;
  background: #3a7ca5;
  transition: width 0.3s ease;
}

.navLink:hover::after,
.navLink.active::after {
  width: 100%;
}
```

## Loading & State Indicators

### Modern Loading States
```css
.skeleton {
  background: linear-gradient(90deg, #f0f0f0 25%, #e0e0e0 50%, #f0f0f0 75%);
  background-size: 200% 100%;
  animation: loading 1.5s infinite;
  border-radius: 0.375rem;
}

@keyframes loading {
  0% { background-position: 200% 0; }
  100% { background-position: -200% 0; }
}
```

### Micro-interactions
```css
.interactive {
  transform-origin: center;
  transition: transform 0.2s ease;
}

.interactive:active {
  transform: scale(0.98);
}

.interactive:hover {
  transform: scale(1.02);
}
```

## Layout Components

### Modern Grid Layouts
```css
.modernGrid {
  display: grid;
  grid-template-columns: repeat(auto-fit, minmax(300px, 1fr));
  gap: 2rem;
  padding: 2rem 0;
}

.modernFlex {
  display: flex;
  flex-wrap: wrap;
  gap: 1.5rem;
  align-items: stretch;
}
```

### Container Queries (Future-proof)
```css
.responsiveContainer {
  container-type: inline-size;
}

@container (min-width: 400px) {
  .responsiveCard {
    flex-direction: row;
    gap: 2rem;
  }
}
```

## Mandatory Modern Features

### 1. Always Include Smooth Transitions
```css
/* Standard transition for interactive elements */
transition: all 0.2s ease;
```

### 2. Use Modern Color Functions
```css
/* RGB with alpha for better color control */
background: rgb(58 124 165 / 0.1);
border-color: hsl(210 20% 90%);
```

### 3. Implement Proper Focus States
Every interactive element must have:
- Visible focus indicators
- Keyboard navigation support
- Sufficient color contrast (4.5:1 minimum)

### 4. Mobile-First Responsive Design
```css
/* Start with mobile styles */
.component {
  padding: 1rem;
}

/* Enhance for larger screens */
@media (min-width: 768px) {
  .component {
    padding: 2rem;
  }
}
```

### 5. Performance Optimizations
- Use `transform` and `opacity` for animations
- Leverage CSS containment when possible
- Minimize layout thrashing with `will-change`

## Component-Specific Guidelines

### Modals & Overlays
- Use backdrop blur effects
- Include smooth entrance/exit animations
- Implement proper focus trapping
- Add click-outside-to-close functionality

### Tables & Data Display
- Use zebra striping with subtle colors
- Add hover states for row highlighting
- Implement sticky headers for long tables
- Include loading states for data fetching

### Forms & Validation
- Show validation states clearly
- Use inline validation with smooth animations
- Include helpful error messages
- Implement progressive enhancement

